## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of online resources and the scope of historical records. Some sources may present a biased perspective, and the complexity of historical events means that not all nuances can be captured in a brief report. Additionally, the lack of firsthand accounts from Native American perspectives limits the depth of understanding regarding the personal and cultural impacts of the Homestead Act. Further research, including primary source analysis and consultation with Native American historians, would provide a more comprehensive view.